Unless you've been living in a fallout bunker (and who would blame you), everyone should know Monday is the day people around the U.S. have been excited about for the past few months. Yes, the total solar eclipse has finally arrived. Photographers across the country captured the phenomenon in various stages with cameras fitted with special filters, along with images of crowds taking in the spectacle. Check out the best photos so far of this rare coast-to-coast event below, and we'll keep updating throughout the day. Share this slide: Get top stories and blog posts emailed to me each day. Newsletters may offer personalized content or advertisements.
